a.desc: Docker - the open-source application container engine

:zap: Open Internet for everyone. Lantern is a free application that delivers fast, reliable and secure access to the open Internet for users in censored regions. It uses a variety of techniques to stay unblocked, including domain fronting, p2p, and pluggable transports.
Gogs (Go Git Service) is a painless self-hosted Git service.
A curated list of awesome Go frameworks, libraries and software
A golang ebook intro how to build a web with golang
Gorgeous metric viz, dashboards & editors for Graphite, InfluxDB & OpenTSDB
A Fast and Flexible Static Site Generator built with love in GoLang
Distributed reliable key-value store for the most critical data of a distributed system
hub helps you win at git.
Scalable datastore for metrics, events, and real-time analytics
beego is an open-source, high-performance web framework for the Go programming language.
Fast, cross-platform HTTP/2 web server with automatic HTTPS
Drone is a Continuous Delivery platform built on Docker, written in Go
Gin is a HTTP web framework written in Go (Golang). It features a Martini-like API with much better performance -- up to 40 times faster. If you need smashing performance, get yourself some Gin.
A Scalable, Survivable, Strongly-Consistent SQL Database
A high productivity, full-stack web framework for the Go language.
Turn any program that uses STDIN/STDOUT into a WebSocket server. Like inetd, but for WebSockets.
Consul is a tool for service discovery, monitoring and configuration.
Share your terminal as a web application

Gor is an open-source tool for capturing and replaying live HTTP traffic into a test environment in order to continuously test your system with real data. It can be used to increase confidence in code deployments, configuration changes and infrastructure changes.
rkt is a container engine for Linux designed to be composable, secure, and built on standards
The Prometheus monitoring system and time series database.
:cherry_blossom: A command-line fuzzy finder written in Go
